se...but reposting it here....<br><br>1. You can multiclass to 1/2 of your current lvl. (ie not to make things unbalancing).<br><br>2. You are only limitied to the spells and abilties of the class of that lvl. Ie a warrior who multi-ed a rogue will not be backstabing like a lvl 60 rogue. He will be backstabing like a lvl 30 rogue, and meleeing as a lvl 60 warrior. (balance)<br><br>3. You can only choose to multiclass a class of your armor type or lower. Ie plate has access to all types of armor. Leather can not multiclass a class that uses plate. Or if you can..there should be a penalty of some sort.<br><br>4. Level advancement is by means of AAxp.<br>lvl 1-10 -&gt; 1aaxp per lvl<br>lvl 11-20 -&gt; 2aaxp per lvl<br>lvl 21-30 -&gt; 4aaxp per lvl<br><br>So a lvl 60 anything can get a lvl 30 multiclass after spending 70aaxp on it. (sounds like a FAIR trade).<br><br>5. Skill caps for abilities that you earn because of your multiclass are capped per lvl based on your multiclass.<br><br>6. You can multiclass MORE than 1 class....Any subsequent classes you choose to multi will cost the aaxp MULTIPLIED by the number of multiclasses you currently have.The lvl of the multiclasses are subject to 1/2 the lvl of your lowest multiclass.<br><br>ie <br>lvl 60 rogue<br>lvl 30 necro (70 points)<br>lvl 15 chanter (20 * 2 = 40 points)<br>lvl 7 cleric (7 * 3 = 21 points)<br>lvl 3 druid (3 * 4 = 12 points)<br>lvl 1 person with no life (1 * 5 = 5 points)<br><br><br>7. Armor type is primary importance. If the armor type you are wearing is NOT compatable with the multiclass, you will NOT have access to the spells/abilities of that class. ie A warrior can not cast enchanter spells, unless the armor he is wearing is enchanter compatable armor ie cloth armour. A rogue would have access to all shaman spells/abilties as the armor types are compatable. A druid would be compatabile with a monk and would get the monks natural abilities(and would be subject to the same wt restrictions as a monk). A warrior would be compatable with a shadownights abilities,whereas he would not be compatable to a monk unless he was wearing only leather type armor. THIS clause is what would make the multiclassing work. <br><br>This kind of Character advance would add a SERIOUS amount of personal customization on each character. The primary classes would NOT be losing out too much, as the other classes are capped to a max of half the lvl. Also with the armor limitations it would force people to be carefull with their choises.<br><br>Personally, as a warrior...I would love a<br><br>60 war<br>30 shadowknight<br>15 cleric<br>7 shaman (have to take off some armor to cast these spells!! hehe)<br><br>but I would have a lvl 30 shadowknight castable fd, self invis, some healing ability, nice spells to be able to taunt, and self speed minor buffs (by taking on and off the armor).<br><br>ohh....the thrills  <br><br>cuch <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2F2F4F><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/uvaraho1.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Varaho1</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/white_fire.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>/cons RED</span><br>  Posts: 398<br> <font color=#FF0000>(7/17/02 6:13:04 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub14.ezboard.com/fthesteelwarriorthetavern.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=953.topic&index=5>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: multiclass</span><hr size=1> So I can't use my gear when using their abilities? Can I at least get to use their gear then? <p><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=170513">Varaho Carnicero</a><BR> 55th Human Myrmidon of the Eternal Bloodguard <BR>Xegony</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/ufoolsfizzelmore.